track_notes: This is a beautiful hike.  I recommend reading the writeup by K7VK.  The trail is well maintained for first 2.5 miles or so, then becomes more challenging.  There are a couple of short scramble sections but nothing too extreme.  It was crazy windy when I activated and the true summit is bald rock, so I set up just below to try to get some shelter and take advantage of trees for the antenna mast.  While I was operating, there were several fly-bys of military jets, they were unbelievably close and flew down into the canyons and tipped wings back and forth, they were obviously having fun.  My total elevation gain on the Garmin was over 3200 feet, with over 2900 on the way up.  I combined this hike with a bushwhack to Diablo Mountains HP (PW-019), leaving the car at the same spot for both hikes.  This made for a very long day with almost 12 miles and around 4500 vertical feet of hiking.
